snippet.title: Vic Mignogna vs. Funimation News Hits MAINSTREAM MEDIA!
snippet.description:
News of anime voice actor Vic Mignogna suing FUNimation, Monica Rial, Jamie Marchi and Ronald Toye is starting to hit the mainstream media outlets. Newsweek, Variety, Screenrant and a few other notable outlets have picked up the story. This is NOT a good look for Funimation's PR. And Elon Musk is using Edward Elric as his avatar on Twitter -- what's THAT all about?!

The court documents -https://www.scribd.com/document/406767091/Plaintiff-s-Original-Petition

Newsweek - https://www.newsweek.com/vic-mignogna-voice-actor-who-plays-broly-dragon-age-movies-games-sues-1401962

Variety - https://variety.com/2019/gaming/news/vic-mignogna-sues-funimation-1203193225/


ANN story - https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-04-19/vic-mignogna-sues-funimation-jamie-marchi-monica-rial-ronald-toye/.145898

Nick Rekieta / Ty Beard stream - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mzP7TdTZHq8
